## Key Finding: Exact v65 Code Diff
Identified the EXACT changes between v65 era and current code in semantic_cog.py:
1. Targeting: v65 used tiered hub_penalty (steep distance-from-hub costs) vs current network_penalty (mild linear)
2. Expansion: v65 used 5.0/30.0 vs current 10.0/60.0
3. Retreat margin: v65 used 15 vs current 20
4. No hotspot tracking in v65

Created AlphaV65TrueReplicaPolicy that uses EXACT v65 targeting function (hub_penalty).

## 5-seed Local Test (5000 steps, 8 agents)
Base (current code): avg 3.29 (1.70, 1.31, 2.23, 4.79, 6.42)
V65 True Replica: avg 3.22 (4.29, 1.70, 1.92, 1.97, 6.24)
- Nearly identical averages
- V65 true helps seed 1 a lot (1.70→4.29), hurts seeds 3-4

## CRITICAL FINDING: Tournament uses variable team sizes!
Pool config: "2+6, 6+2, 4+4" — NOT 8v8!
Base policy assumes 8 agents, allocates 5 pressure → no miners with 2-4 agents.

## Variable Team Size Results (3 seeds each)
| Team size | Base    | Team-aware | V65+TeamAware |
|-----------|---------|------------|---------------|
| 2 agents  | 0.03    | 0.08       | 0.04          |
| 4 agents  | 0.28    | 1.14       | 1.51          |
| 6 agents  | 1.90    | 2.08       | 0.98          |
| 8 agents  | 1.75    | -          | 2.31          |

Key insights:
- Team-aware policies MASSIVELY outperform base at 4 agents (1.14 vs 0.28)
- V65+TeamAware best at 4 agents (1.51) but worse at 6 (0.98)
- 2-agent games are very hard regardless

